 \subsection{Corollary} {\em The theory of the multisorted representations structure is superstable. The $U$-rank of a non-principal 1-type of sort ${\mathrm{Sp}}_K$ is $1,$ the $U$-rank of a 1-type  of $A_K$ containing the formula ${\mathrm{pr}}(v)=p$ over $p\in {\mathrm{Sp}}_K$ is $0$ or $1$ depending on whether $p$ is finite or infinite prime. If the type contains no such formula, it is generic and its $U$-rank is 2.}

 \medskip

 Indeed, by (\ref{3.9b}) for any $N$ the set of $1$-types over $N$ of sorts  ${\mathrm{Sp}}_K$ is at most of cardinality continuum. Moreover, each $0$-definable non-principal type has a unique non-algebraic extension over  $N.$

  A type of sort $A_K$ by \ref{3.7}  is determined by a type of sort ${\mathrm{Sp}}_K$ and the type relative to the $\omega$-stable substructure ${\mathrm{cl}}(a).$ If a 1-type contains a formula ${\mathrm{pr}}(v)=p$ for a parameter $p,$ then it is a type of an element of the fibre $\mathrm{Fb}_p,$ which is either finite, if $p$ is finite, or strongly minimal, so of $U$-rank 1.  The unique complete 1-type which negates all formulas ${\mathrm{pr}}(v)=p$ is of $U$-rank 2.\qed   

